      {
         "id": "SECTION_introduction",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Introduction\n\nDuring our school years, we learn to name everything around us through words. As we advance in our studies, we realize that these words sometimes have more than one meaning. Depending on the family’s financial situation, if a person has the opportunity to continue studying, they may also discover that the meanings of words change over time (<htcite0>).\n\nThis lack of knowledge can lead us to make different interpretation errors, which brings us to our first reflection:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "79ea767b-924d-43e3-9bea-a8195b536dde",
                     "text": "Sabino, Marilei A.",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2011",
                        "month": "-1",
                        "day": "-1"
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: I Was Mistaken</b><br /><br />Have you ever used current knowledge to interpret events from the past, only to later realize that you misunderstood the text?<br /><br />Have you ever thought that a word you use every day might not have the same meaning it had thousands of years ago?</div></div></center>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_definition",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Definition\n\nBefore studying some specific cases of anachronism, we must clearly define what anachronism means. To do this, we turn to the Britannica Dictionary (<htcite0>):",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 0,
                     "uuid": "5a65ee5a-3954-4f90-998f-4061301fa425",
                     "text": "The Britannica Dictionary",
                     "page": "anachronism",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "",
                        "year": "",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><ul class=\"citation\"><li><i>1. something (such as a word, an object, or an event) that is mistakenly placed in a time where it does not belong in a story, movie, etc.</i></li></ul></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_lab_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_lab question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-microscope\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_lab\"><b>Practice 1: I Wasn’t There</b><br />We are now in the year <htdate0>.<br /><br />Now, take a sheet of paper and a pen, and describe how you witnessed the first arrival of K’inich Yax K’uk’ Mo’ when he took control of Copán, in Honduras (<i>Abya Yala</i>), around the year <htdate1> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('85c2d88c-6ad8-4858-95f8-0f157c49bf07'); return false;\">Hutnick, Anastasia, <htdate2>, pp. 36</a>; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('642c83dc-6a59-49c0-b728-b44ca1036fac'); return false;\">History Tracers Team, <htdate3>, Indígenas Copán</a>).</div></div></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": [
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "now",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "378",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2020",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  },
                  {
                     "type": "gregory",
                     "year": "2025",
                     "month": "-1",
                     "day": "-1"
                  }
               ],
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "**Practice 1** presents a possible anachronism if the text is written as a newspaper article or magazine report, as if you had actually witnessed the event. This occurs because, for someone to have seen the conquest of Copán, they would have had to be born before the year <htdate0>—and if still alive today, they would be over <spam id=\"iage\"></spam> years old.\n\nOn the other hand, if **Practice 1** is written in the form of a poem or short story, the account would not be considered an anachronism, since it would involve a kind of abstraction that is common in literature (<htcite0>).",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
